Git Environment on Mac OS X


brew install git bash-completion


Configure Global Variables 

git config --global user.name "Git User"
git config --global user.email "email@example.com"


Generate SSH key

ssh-keygen


Copy Key

cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub | pbcopy


Configure Highlight

[color]
	branch = auto
	diff = auto
	status = auto
[color "branch"]
	current = yellow reverse
	local = yellow
	remote = green
[color "diff"]
	meta = yellow bold
	frag = magenta bold
	old = red bold
	new = green bold
[color "status"]
	added = yellow
	changed = green
	untracked = red


Create a ~/.gitexcludes file and directory:
.gitexcludes remove file global in localhost

